	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Note that if you have CHR-RAM it's always possible to flip tiles in software. I know it still wastes VRAM, but at least it doesn't waste ROM.</div>
<br />I've seen SMS games doing that with sprites. When copying the tiles from ROM to VRAM, a 256-byte long table was used to flip every byte during the copy for horizontal flipping. Also, I believe they read the tiles upside down (bottom row first) for vertical flipping.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
